Using a chip clip is the best way I can think.  You'd want to power the cart edge with 5V though that way you weren't running off battery power during programming.  It's kind of a hack job idea though.  Lots of effort with all those wires and high chance of failure...<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4832">infiniteneslives</a> — Fri Jan 06, 2012 5:47 am</p><hr />
