<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8501&amp;p=88520#p88520"><![CDATA[
You need some sort of dumper something like the CopyNES, Kazzo, or similar.  <br /><br />Really the .sav file is a raw dump of the WRAM from what I understand.  If you got tricky with a EPROM programmer or something you could actually make something work if you made use of a chip clip or something.  <br /><br />You might be able to find someone to help you get the job done if you don't own a dumper and don't plan on acquiring one.  I could help out but I don't know how expeditious I'd be.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4832">infiniteneslives</a> — Thu Jan 05, 2012 11:26 pm</p><hr />
